data.value:
Valid values are: IMPLICIT, EXPLICIT.
In IMPLICIT Clustering, load balancers are configured with persistence rules and there is no need for data sharing across nodes (recommended for best scalability and performance).
In EXPLICIT Clustering, load balancers are not used for routing data. Instead, data is stored as a common in-memory view across all nodes.
